2003-05-19 21:43  hannes

	* components/transformers/xforms.xsl:

	
	-Added htmlArea stuff, now you can use <xforms:textarea class="htmlarea" which will transform a simple textarea
	into a WYSIWYG area using http://www.interactivetools.com/products/htmlarea/
	
	-htmlArea can be configured in the xforms text, see MyGyndoc for example
	
	-Added possibilty to use <xforms:value class="default">some default value</xforms:value> for textareas, htmlareas and simple input fields.
	This value is used when no other xforms:value is given.
	
