2003-02-19 11:29  chregu

	* components/cache.php:

	reimplementation of metaObject and validityObject stroing implenatation.
	- globals (and later headers) are stored as userdate with the cached data,
	  -> they are only loaded, if cache miss or at the end of the pipeline
	- validityObject is stillstored in the .meta file, but in an assoc array
	   for later extension
	
	so, delete your cache before trying this out.
	
	and, you need tha latest PEAR::Cache package (1.5.3, released today), otherwise
	it won't accept userdata longer than 256 chars, which is too short for our
	needs.
	
2003-02-19 09:00  chregu

	* components/cache.php:

	store all "meta" data in one file (validityObject and globals till now, later
	headers) -> less files -> less loads -> less overhead ;)
	- will change the function names a little bit, as they are missleading now
	
