2002-12-01 18:36  hannes

	* components/transformers/phpprocessor.php:

	
	Overwrites caching-methodes inherited 'transformer' to make this component uncachable.
	
2002-12-01 18:21  hannes

	* components/transformer.php:

	
	Caching stuff, implements cachable interface now.
	
2002-12-01 18:02  hannes

	* components/serializer.php:

	
	
	Now implements 'cachable'.
	Caution: This means that all serializers look like they were cachable! This, of course, is not the case. So
	non-cachable components must overwrite check/generateValidty and make them return false!
	
2002-12-01 17:36  hannes

	* components/component.php:

	
	
	Added default methods for the 'cachable' interface (generateKeyDefault(), generateValidityDefault() and
	checkValidityDefault()). These are used by many of the file-based cachable components.
	
2002-12-01 17:28  hannes

	* sitemap/sitemap2php.xsl:

	
	
	Added component caching stuff for readers, generators, transformers and serializers.
	Note that in the  current state, a pipeline marked cachable must consist but of cachable components.
	We probably need a way to allow also halfway-cachable pipelines.
	
2002-12-01 17:01  hannes

	* sitemap/sitemap.php:

	
	
	Added methods to turn on and off caching
	
2002-12-01 16:55  hannes

	* components/generators/xmlfile.php:

	
	
	Made this component cachable. In other words it now implements the 'cachable' interface by providing
	- generateValidity()
	- checkValidity()
	- generateKey()
	
2002-12-01 15:38  hannes

	* components/cache.php:

	
	
	This is the very first version of component caching for popoon. The intention is described in slide 23 in
	http://chregu.tv/popoon/pres/, for more details have a look at http://bugzilla.bitflux.ch/show_bug.cgi?id=23.
	To use this you have to add the attribute cachable='yes' and cachedir=.. to the map:pipeline tag in your sitemap.xml.
	Note that you must only use components implementing the 'Cachable' interface in a pipeline marked cachable.
	Ill'try to make cachable as many components as possible in the next days.
	Please not that this is also the very first time I add something to a CVS repository, so please excuse if it's all
	wrong.
	
